Nine Cabinet Secretaries were sworn-in on Friday following their appointment by President Uhuru Kenyatta. Margaret Kobia (Public Service and Youth), John Munyes (Mining), Farida Karoney (Lands), Peter Munya (East African Community) and Monica Juma (Foreign Affairs) were among those who took the oath at State House in Nairobi. The others were former DPP Keriako Tobiko (Environment and Forestry), Simon Chelugui (Water), former Marsabit Governor Ukur Yatani (Labour) and Rashid Achesa (Sports). The President witnessed the ceremony. Kobia who was the first to lift the Bible, sign documents and shake Uhuru's hand. "I ... will commit to my secrecy as a Cabinet Secretary... I will perform the functions of my office to the best of my ability...so help me God..." she swore. Then came Munyes, Juma, Tobiko, Karoney, Munya, Yattani, Achesa and Chelugui in that order. Read: MPs approve Uhuru's Cabinet nominees Also read: Chelugui richest Cabinet nominee with Sh796m net worth, Tobiko at Sh360m - report Click here for the latest political stories   